---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ImagePlaceholder from '../components/ImagePlaceholder.astro';
import { pathFor } from '../i18n/ui';

const locale = 'en' as const;
const title = 'The founder';
const description = 'Founder of BeyondBorderGroup, HubStudio, and Nuvora Studio. Twenty-five years in digital and eCommerce on both sides of the China and West bridge.';
---

<Layout locale={locale} route="founder" title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="hero-editorial hero-editorial--dark">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split split--text-first">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--on-dark">The founder</span>
          <h1 class="hero-editorial__title balance">One operator. Two decades on both sides.</h1>
          <p class="hero-editorial__lead">
            BeyondBorderGroup is founded and led by Cyril Drouin. The group exists because he has spent
            twenty-five years building brands on both sides of the China and West bridge, and watched the same
            companies hit the same walls in both directions. Every agency in the ecosystem is the codification of
            something he had to build for a client at least once.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ImagePlaceholder ratio="4x5" label="Editorial founder portrait." dark />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">Why the group exists</span>
      <h2 class="balance">Two kinds of rooms over two decades.</h2>
      <p>The thesis is not theoretical. It comes from sitting in two kinds of rooms over two decades.</p>
      <p>
        The first kind: a Western CMO in Paris, asking why the China launch is not converting after six months
        and a translated website.
      </p>
      <p>
        The second kind: a Chinese factory owner in Shenzhen, asking why the leads from Berlin are not coming
        after the Geneva trade show.
      </p>
      <p>
        Same question. Mirrored sides. Different infrastructure. And in both cases, the gap was never language.
        It was brand, channels, web, content, and who picks up the phone.
      </p>
      <p>
        He built BeyondBorderGroup to run the full chain on both sides, with specialist teams who actually live
        inside the destination market.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header">
        <span class="eyebrow">Background</span>
        <h2 class="balance">Twenty-five years in digital, communication, and eCommerce.</h2>
      </header>
      <div class="grid-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card__title">Languages and education</h3>
          <p>Master's in IT and mathematics. Native French. Fluent English. Working command of Chinese.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card__title">Publicis North Asia</h3>
          <p>
            Former Chief Digital and eCommerce Officer for Publicis North Asia. Led the practice across Google,
            Amazon, Instagram, Facebook, Tmall, JD, WeChat, and the rest of the Chinese platform stack.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card__title">Independent agency</h3>
          <p>
            Founder of his own agency across Europe and North Asia. Focus on digital transformation, eCommerce
            technologies (Gold Partner with Adobe, Salesforce, and leading open-source platforms), and media
            planning and buying across major platforms and ad exchanges.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3 class="card__title">HubStudio and Nuvora Studio</h3>
          <p>
            Founder of HubStudio, the AIGC-native content studio that powers every agency in the ecosystem.
            Founder of Nuvora Studio, the LinkedIn-only B2B agency that powers the LinkedIn module inside
            BeyondBridge.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split">
        <div class="prose">
          <span class="eyebrow">Brands</span>
          <h2 class="balance">Brands he has built for, across two decades, on both sides of the bridge.</h2>
          <p>
            Apple. GSK. Estée Lauder. Bacardi. Bayer. Sanofi. L’Oréal. Danone. Lenovo. Beiersdorf. Nike. Ferrero.
            Colgate. Heineken. Nestlé. Pigeon. Siemens. Kering.
          </p>
          <p class="muted">
            Mixed list, deliberately. Western brands he took into China. Asian brands he scaled across the
            region. Global brands where the work crossed both sides at once.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="prose">
          <span class="eyebrow">Industry roles and certifications</span>
          <h2 class="balance">Where else his name shows up.</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Certified in Google Ads, Google Analytics, Amazon Advertising, LinkedIn.</li>
            <li>Jury member for Adfest and the DMAA International Digital Marketing Awards.</li>
            <li>Chair of the Communication and Marketing Forum, European Union Chamber of Commerce in China. Seven years.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="split split--media-first">
        <ImagePlaceholder ratio="4x5" label="Lecture hall. Cyril teaching executive MBA." />
        <div class="prose">
          <span class="eyebrow">Teaching</span>
          <h2 class="balance">Ten-plus years teaching digital and eCommerce.</h2>
          <p>To executive MBA students at:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>HEC, Paris.</li>
            <li>ESSEC, Paris and Singapore.</li>
            <li>ESMOD, Paris.</li>
            <li>Shanghai Jiaotong University.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Regular keynote speaker on digital and eCommerce worldwide. The training programmes inside
            BeyondBorderGroup, the masterclasses, the executive workshops, and the China learning expeditions
            come directly from this teaching practice.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">Why this matters for clients</span>
      <h2 class="balance">An operator who still runs the practice.</h2>
      <p>
        Most agency founders are either operators or salespeople. Cyril is an operator who still runs the
        practice. He sits in the strategy sessions for the agencies in the group. He wrote the playbooks the
        teams now execute. When a client asks "has this been done before?", the answer is usually "yes. We did
        it for Apple. Or Estée Lauder. Or Heineken. Or a Chinese brand most people have not heard of yet."
      </p>
      <p>
        That continuity is the point. The group is not six independent vendors that share a logo. It is six
        specialist teams that share a thesis, a leadership group, and an operating standard. Set by someone who
        has built brands across the China and West border, in both directions, for twenty-five years.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--dark">
    <div class="container container--narrow center">
      <h2 class="balance">Connect.</h2>
      <div class="btn-row" style="justify-content: center;">
        <a class="btn btn--primary" href={pathFor('contact', locale)}>Book a call with Cyril</a>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost-light" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/cyril-d-68835729" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
